Finance minister Tito Mboweni will be delivering the highly anticipated, annual National Budget Speech today, and will outline the government’s spending and revenue collection for the year ahead. This Budget affects both businesses and consumers in a myriad of ways, which is why it’s imperative that businesses and consumers learn to balance their income and expenses effectively. For this year’s Budget Speech, FNB is focusing on what counts – you, your family, your business, and your future. Find out how FNB will help empower you for your best year yet! #20MINEteen #FNBBudgetSpeech2019  This article was published in partnership with FNB.